<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3516] Fix introduced for GROOVY-3436 created a situation that can result in a stackoverflowerror with some groovy config objects</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3516</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following config causes the config slurper to create an object that subsequently causes a stackoverflow error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the root cause starts here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/russel/groovy/commit/05248f609f805d9a467a6fa6bd07dacaa71a71ef#L1R221&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://github.com/russel/groovy/commit/05248f609f805d9a467a6fa6bd07dacaa71a71ef#L1R221&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def cfg = &quot;&quot;&quot;
smc{
  pages{
    smc {
      type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;smcAdminPage&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    }
  }
}
&quot;&quot;&quot;

ConfigObject c = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ConfigSlurper().parse(cfg)

print c
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
